The '''Heino Eller Tartu Music College''' is a [[music school]] in [[Tartu]], [[Estonia]], founded in 1919<ref name="EKA">{{cite web|title=Elleri kooli ajaloost|url=http://www.tmk.ee/uldinfo/ajalugu|website=Heino Elleri nimeline Tartu Muusikakool|accessdate=4 March 2018}}</ref>. It got its current name in 1971, after the Estonian composer and music teacher [[Heino Eller]], who taught in the school from 1920 until 1940<ref name="EKA" />.
== Tartu School of Composition == [[Heino Eller]]'s return to [[Tartu]] in 1920, to teach in the Tartu Music School, led to the development in the 1920s–1930s of the '''Tartu school of composition'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Heino Eller ja Tartu koolkond|url=http://www.ooper.parnu.ee/emf/EMF_tekst/HUMAL_HEINO_ELLER_JA_TARTU_KOOLKOND.htm||last=Humal|first=Mart|website=Eesti muusika foorum|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>
Those identified with the school included: * Composers ** [[Heino Eller]] (originator) ** [[Eduard Tubin]] ** [[Eduard Oja]] ** [[Olav Roots]] ** [[Alfred Karindi]] ** [[Johannes Bleive]] * Music theorists ** [[Karl Leichter]]
